FBIS4-64977 "drweu091_g_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-091 Daily Report 10 May 1994 CANADA Legislation Presented To Patrol Grand Banks Fisheries Legislation Presented To Patrol Grand Banks Fisheries LD1005211294 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 2030 GMT 10 May 94 LD1005211294 Montreal Radio Canada International English BFN [Excerpt] Canada is cracking down on foreign ships fishing outside the 200 mile limit on the east coast. The minister of fisheries, Brian Tobin, presented legislation in the House of Commons today to protect the Grand Banks. If passed by parliament the law would allow fisheries officers to board foreign ships, search them, and bring them back to a Canadian port to face charges. Fines could reach a million dollars. [passage omitted]
